---
export async function getStaticPaths() {
	const paths = ['en', 'pt'].map((lang) => ({
		params: { lang },
	}));
	return paths;
}

import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About Agro2Code Blog" description="Agro2Code Blog is the editorial extension of the Agro2Code portfolio.">
<Layout
	title="About Agro2Code Blog"
	description="Agro2Code Blog is the editorial extension of the Agro2Code portfolio."
	author="Mateus Campos"
	pubDate={new Date('March 04 2026')}
	heroImage="/agro2code-blog/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Agro2Code Blog is the editorial layer of the Agro2Code portfolio. The portfolio introduces topics
		and this blog expands each subject through complete articles, technical notes, ideas, and
		discussions.
	</p>

	<p>
		The project is intentionally simple in architecture and strong in process: content is written in
		an external Obsidian vault, validated by a publication script, and published as static routes in
		Astro.
	</p>

	<p>
		Current priorities are publication flow reliability, multilingual consistency between EN and PT,
		and stable canonical URLs to keep portfolio integration predictable over time.
	</p>

	<p>
		This blog follows incremental delivery with TDD and a GitHub-based CI/CD flow. The goal is to
		evolve safely, keeping architecture decisions documented and publication operations efficient.
	</p>

	<p>
		As the platform grows, the same principle remains: clear editorial contracts, small reliable
		changes, and content quality first.
	</p>
</Layout>
</Base>
